image.altText: A bushfire burning in a Queensland national park

items.synopsis: Queensland authorities are bracing for dangerous fire conditions, with seven districts facing the likelihood of high fire danger by the end of this week. Four fires blazed across the state yesterday, damaging properties and causing some residents to flee their homes.

title.children: After a fiery weekend in Queensland, bushfire warnings are set to intensify this week

title.children: Pet python surfing session costs owner thousands after wildlife officers chase up viral footage

image.altText: A man in a suit is interviewed for television.

items.synopsis: One of the taxpayers helped by ATO whistleblower Richard Boyle has spoken out for the first time, describing the prosecution of the person who gave him a lifeline as "insanity". Mr Boyle's wife has also spoken to 7.30 about the toll the six-year-long ordeal has taken on the couple.

title.children: Richard Boyle faces the prospect of four decades in jail. His wife says all he did was tell the truth

image.altText: Chris Bowen in a navy suit and tie in  front of the australian flag at a press conference

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: If current losses hold, Aussie tech stocks could see their biggest fall since August 25, after dipping by 2.8% this morning. The fall in Australian tech stocks follows the losses on Wall Street on Friday, with the Nasdaq down 1.6% after chipmakers and megacap growth companies dropped. Software company Xero has fallen by as much as 4.1% so far, while WiseTech Global and Altium have slid by as much as 2.9% and 2.7% respectively. It's certainly one to keep an eye on throughout the day, that's for sure 👀

liveBlogPostPrepared.plaintext: Whitehaven Coal has issued a statement on the ASX confirming it i s in talks to buy the Daunia and Blackwater coal mines in Queensland from the BHP Mitsubishi Alliance. The statement from the mining company follows a report in today's Australian Financial Review, and says the process is "ongoing". "As communicated in Whitehaven's FY23 Results Announcement on 24 August, Whitehaven's share buy-back has been temporarily suspended while the company is considering application of its capital allocation framework in light of growth opportunities," the company said. " Whitehaven confirms that those opportunities include the Daunia and Blackwater mines. "Whitehaven will continue to keep the market informed in accordance with its continuous disclosure obligations."
liveBlogPostPrepared.title: Whitehaven Coal in talks to buy Queensland coal mines
